         <xocs:funding-text>We extend gratitude to A. Kahmen for his foundational fieldwork that we built this study upon, and to K. Byrne and C. Cuellar-Gempeler (Cal Poly Humboldt University), as well as Je\u0148\u00FDk Hofmeister (Czech University of Life Sciences), for their ecological and editorial insight and advice. We thank those who helped with planning (L. McCrigler, S. Morrison, and T. Hooker) and collecting field data (J. Ingalls, C. Copper, and J. Felt). Statistical code and advice were provided by P. Bourdeau, A. Buchheister, R. Overholser, and G. Simpson. Financial support was provided by the Native Plant Society of Oregon, Cal Poly Humboldt RSCA , Biology Graduate Student Association , and the Czech University of Life Sciences grant IGA ( A_18_25 ). </xocs:funding-text>
      </xocs:funding-list>
