         <ce:floats>
            <ce:figure id="fig0005">
               <ce:label>Fig. 1</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0005">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0005" view="all">Location of the study area of the Sucker Creek watershed within Josephine County, Oregon, USA.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0005" role="short">Fig. 1</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0005" locator="gr1" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112725006565/gr1"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="fig0010">
               <ce:label>Fig. 2</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0010">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0010" view="all">The canopy cover of each developmental stage and stand age in 2003 and 2021. The data points represent the plot-level canopy cover to show variation within developmental stages. In each sample year column, boxplots are in the order of early seral (ES), mature (M), and old growth (OG) from left to right. The symbol “*” denotes marginally significant (0.05 &lt; <ce:italic>P</ce:italic> &lt; 0.1) change in stage between years based on Wilcoxon test (<ce:cross-ref id="cr0005" refid="tbl0010">Table 2</ce:cross-ref>). Post hoc letters are provided where there were significant Kruskal Wallis results (<ce:cross-ref id="cr0010" refid="tbl0015">Table 3</ce:cross-ref>), and values with the same letters do not differ significantly. The light gray dashed line is a reference for comparing box plots and not based on a calculated value.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0010" role="short">Fig. 2</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0010" locator="gr2" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112725006565/gr2"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="fig0015">
               <ce:label>Fig. 3</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0015">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0015" view="all">The richness, evenness, and Shannon diversity of each developmental stage and stand age in 2003 and 2021. The boxplots of each developmental stage are created using the values of the response calculated from the mean-cover of plant species on the plot-scale. The data points represent the plot-level values to show variation within developmental stages. The symbol “*” denotes marginally significant (0.05 &lt; <ce:italic>P</ce:italic> &lt; 0.1) change in stage between years based on Wilcoxon test (<ce:cross-ref id="cr0015" refid="tbl0010">Table 2</ce:cross-ref>). Post hoc letters are provided where there were significant Kruskal Wallis results (<ce:cross-ref id="cr0020" refid="tbl0015">Table 3</ce:cross-ref>), and values with the same letters do not differ significantly. The light gray dashed line in each plot is a reference for comparing box plots and not based on a calculated value. In each sample year column, boxplots are in the order of early seral (ES), mature (M), and old growth (OG) from left to right.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0015" role="short">Fig. 3</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0015" locator="gr3" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112725006565/gr3"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="fig0020">
               <ce:label>Fig. 4</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0020">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0020" view="all">Response plots for species richness, evenness, diversity, and beta diversity GAMMs (y-axis) for each sample year (green = 2003, gray = 2021). <ce:italic>P</ce:italic>-values are listed in order of sample year where both occur. Partial effects of significant predictors are displayed (<ce:italic>α</ce:italic> ≤ 0.05), as well as predictors with marginal significance (<ce:italic>α</ce:italic> = 0.05 – 0.1). Summary results of each GAMM are reported in Appendix <ce:cross-ref id="cr0025" refid="sec0110">Table S4</ce:cross-ref>.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0020" role="short">Fig. 4</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0020" locator="gr4" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112725006565/gr4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="fig0025">
               <ce:label>Fig. 5</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0025">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0025" view="all">NMDS ordination of understory species across a chronosequence of 13 stands in two sample years of 2003 and 2021(<ce:italic>n</ce:italic> = 26). The colors represent the three developmental stages: orange = early seral (ES); blue = mature (M); green = old growth (OG). The lines of the ellipses represent the sample year: dashed line = 2003; solid line = 2021. The black arrows represent the shift across the 18-year period, and the dashed arrow represents the shift in the youngest plot, plot 1. Stand attributes are placed on the direction of the NMDS axis that represent correlations with ordination scores where <ce:italic>r</ce:italic> value ≥ 0.45 (<ce:cross-ref id="cr0030" refid="tbl0025">Table 5</ce:cross-ref>).</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0025" role="short">Fig. 5</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0025" locator="gr5" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112725006565/gr5"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="fig0030">
               <ce:label>Fig. 6</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0030">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0030" view="all">NMDS ordination of understory species trait of shade tolerance across the chronosequence of 13 plots with 20 subplots in each sample year (2003 and 2021; <ce:italic>n</ce:italic> = 520). The colors represent the three developmental stages: orange = early seral, blue = mature, and green = old growth. The lines of the ellipses represent the sample year: dashed line = 2003 and solid line = 2021. The black arrows represent the direction of the shift in composition in the plot across the 18-year period. Stand attributes are placed in the direction of the NMDS axis that represent correlations with ordination scores where <ce:italic>r</ce:italic> value ≥ 0.45 (<ce:cross-ref id="cr0035" refid="tbl0035">Table 7</ce:cross-ref>). Species are displayed at their maximum abundance and are coded by shade tolerance: H = high (red circle), I = intermediate (black triangle), and L = low (blue cross).</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0030" role="short">Fig. 6</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0030" locator="gr6" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112725006565/gr6"/>
            </ce:figure>
