               <ce:label>Table 7</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0065">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0065" view="all">Summary of results from Indicator Species Analysis. The bold values have significant (<ce:italic>α</ce:italic> ≤ 0.05) strength of association (i.e., Indicator Value, IV) that is calculated from the specificity and fidelity of a species to the developmental stage. Selected marginally significant species associations were included in the table to give further insight into species associations with developmental stages such as the Mature grouping where there were no significant indicator species. The plant guild of the species is represented by the following abbreviations: H-herb, S- (sub)shrub, G- graminoid, and F- fern. Developmental stages represented as ES = early seral; M = mature; O = old growth.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0065" role="short">Table 7</ce:alt-text>
               <tgroup cols="7">
                  <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
                  <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
                  <colspec colnum="3" colname="col3"/>
                  <colspec colnum="4" colname="col4"/>
                  <colspec colnum="5" colname="col5"/>
                  <colspec colnum="6" colname="col6"/>
                  <colspec colnum="7" colname="col7"/>
                  <thead>
                     <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" role="colgroup" namest="col1" nameend="col7">Indicator species analysis</entry>
                     </row>
                  </thead>
